Two More Air-Traffic Controllers Caught Sleeping, FAA Says

-- B y   J o h n   H u g h e s
-- 
2011-05-24T20:37:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/two-more-air-traffic-controllers-caught-sleeping-faa-says.html
Two more U.S. air-traffic controllers
were caught sleeping in January at their posts in  Los Angeles 
and  Fort Worth ,  Texas , Federal Aviation administration chief
 Randy Babbitt  told reporters.  One of the workers was reprimanded and the other is still
being investigated in incidents revealed recently to top agency
executives as part of a national review, Babbitt said after a
Senate hearing today in  Washington .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter J. Brennan at 
 pbrennan3@bloomberg.net  